What is Semiconductor Back‑End Process Equipment?
Semiconductor back‑end processing represents the final manufacturing stages that transform finished dies into fully functional, market‑ready products. After wafer fabrication (front‑end), chips undergo a series of back‑end steps: wafer‑level packaging, die‑attach, wire‑bonding, flip‑chip assembly, encapsulation, and final test. The equipment used in these steps must deliver sub‑micron alignment accuracy, ultra‑high throughput, and precise thermal management to meet the relentless miniaturization and performance targets of modern electronics.
