Key Market Drivers
1. Accelerated Adoption of Advanced Packaging Technologies
The shift toward fan‑out wafer‑level packaging (FO‑WLP), chip‑on‑wafer (CoW), and heterogeneous integration is creating a surge in demand for high‑precision die‑attach, encapsulation, and testing platforms. These solutions enable higher I/O density, lower form factors, and improved electrical performance, which are critical for AI accelerators, high‑performance computing (HPC), and 5G infrastructure.
2. Rising Complexity of Chip Testing for AI, 5G, and Automotive
Modern devices require exhaustive validation of speed, power, and functional safety. Test equipment that can perform high‑speed parametric testing, reliability burn‑in, and AI‑driven defect prediction is increasingly essential, prompting fabs to upgrade to next‑generation test systems.
